.\" termin.al-name: blog
.\" termin.al-usage: blog
.\" termin.al-summary: Open blog content.
.TH BLOG 1 "" "termin.al" "termin.al Manual"
.ftr B R
.ftr I R
.ftr BI R
.SH NAME
blog \- Open blog content.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
blog
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
Opens the published entries beneath
.B ~/blog
as a hierarchical collection. Publication titles, dates and collection paths come from validated metadata; selecting an entry opens its rendered document and returning restores the collection selection.
.SH VIEWER
Use j/k or the arrows to move, h/l or left/right to collapse and expand, g/G or Home/End to jump, Enter to toggle a branch or open an entry, and / to filter. Escape leaves the filter input first; from the collection, q, Escape or Ctrl+C returns to the owning shell. Mobile controls expose movement, filtering, opening and Shell return.
.SH FAILURES
Extra arguments are rejected. Missing or misclassified publication content produces the stable content-unavailable diagnostic. Cancellation opens nothing.
.SH LIMITS
Collection loading traverses at most 100 virtual entries to a maximum depth of 100. The bounded collection does not read outside
.BR ~/blog .
.SH NOTES
The collection and opened documents are transient pane presentation. Closing them preserves the shell transcript, history and working directory.
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
$ blog
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
notes(1), projects(1), open(1)
